{
  "query": "What are the potential benefits and negative consequences of abandoning management on grasslands for butterfly and moth populations?",
  "relevant_summary": "Across studies of ceasing grazing or mowing on grasslands, community composition of butterflies and moths was often similar to managed sites, but after 6 years of abandonment communities became dominated by generalist species with fewer generations per year [3956][3957]. Species richness frequently remained similar to managed grasslands, sometimes increased after 4\u201310 years of abandonment or when meadows were left uncut for a summer, but was often lower after longer periods (e.g., >10\u201320 years or >50 years) or compared to traditional rotational mowing and burning [3956][3957]. Abundance responses were mixed: in some cases abandonment (from weeks to 25 years) increased total butterflies, day\u2011flying or nocturnal moths, Scotch argus, caterpillars, and small insects, and uncut or temporarily abandoned meadows had higher abundances than annually or frequently mown sites [3956][3957]. In other cases, abandonment for 1\u201320 years reduced overall butterflies or some species and caterpillars relative to mowing once or twice per year, with some time\u2011since\u2011abandonment effects (e.g., higher densities 2\u20139 years after cessation than >10 years or currently grazed) and species\u2011specific mixed responses [3956][3957]. Abandonment tended to increase woodland and hedgerow butterflies and burnet moths, but decrease grassland or farmland species, and extinctions of large blue and silver\u2011studded blue occurred in some abandoned meadows; heath fritillary abundance was similar around six years post\u2011abandonment but lower with no caterpillars after >25 years [3956][3957]. Behavioural/use responses included similar occurrence of hoary bell moth caterpillars and similar frequency of marsh fritillary webs in abandoned vs managed sites, but reduced occurrence of grizzled skipper and painted lady and increased occurrence of small pearl\u2011bordered fritillary in abandoned meadows [3956][3957].",
